{
  "texts": [
    "Novel approaches have been explored to fine-tune LLMs for APR, including standard neural machine translation (NMT) fine-tuning [20,32], multi-objective fine-tuning [102], incorporating additional information such as code review to enhance fine-tuning [67], augmenting fine-tuning datasets with syntactically diverse but semantically equivalent code [24], utilizing optimal code representations [75] and parameter-efficient techniques are also adopted for effective and low-cost fine-tuning [75,102,116], each aiming to enhance program repair capabilities through LLM fine-tuning.The access to extensive datasets has enabled LLMs to unleash their potential to learn complex patterns and nuances in different scenarios.",
    "Researchers for a long period have been mining public communities millions of code samples in the form of bug-fix pairs to enhance the repairing ability of their approaches [33,83].",
    "LLM-based APR is further improved by fine-tuning with carefully curated open-source data.",
    "Moreover, researchers and developers use synthetic data generated by models to enhance fine-tuning and satisfy specific needs [37,87,95].",
    "By fine-tuning with a variety of data, the LLMs are capable of repairing bugs across different bug types, scenarios, and programming languages [28,106,110]."
  ]
}